50|$|It is {{important}} to note that although some cycles have a typical combustion location (internal or external), they often can be implemented with the other. For example, John Ericsson developed an external <b>heated</b> <b>engine</b> running on a cycle very much like the earlier Diesel cycle. In addition, externally <b>heated</b> <b>engines</b> can often be implemented in open or closed cycles.|$|R
